@Josh Mandel, Bob's successfully merging into Main, but there's no build happening. What we're seeing in committers/notification is this:
HL7/fhir-sdoh-clinicalcare: master rebuilt
Commit: Merge pull request #11 from HL7/RCD

But no links to the build and apparently no build created. (FYI @Robert Dieterle )
Thanks for the note -- I'll look into this today. Just to make sure I understand exactly what we're talking about, this is the HL7/fhir-sdoh-clinicalcare repo, master branch?

http://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/fhir-sdoh-clinicalcare/ is showing me in the footer that it was successfully built today. http://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/fhir-sdoh-clinicalcare/build.log has the logs. Can you let me know what looks off so I can further investigate?
You're right. It does seem to be building, but the message in the #committers/notification stream seems odd - no links
Yeah, looks like several notification messages lack a "details" line with links.
Uh, never mind -- this search shows all of the relevant build notifications for hl7/fhir-sdoh-clinicalcare, and each has a "details" line and links.
@Lloyd McKenzie are you seeing something different?
